Use the standard library
This is how to find_closest_elements of numbers:
   Remember that n is numbers's length
   Remember that best_a is item 0 in numbers
   Remember that best_b is item 1 in numbers
   Remember that best_d is abs of (diff of best_a and best_b)
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that a is item i in numbers
      Remember that j is sum of i and 1
      Remember that remain is diff of n and j
      Do this remain times:
         Remember that b is item j in numbers
         Remember that d is abs of (diff of a and b)
         When d is less than best_d, then:
            Remember that best_d is d
            Remember that best_a is a
            Remember that best_b is b
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is [best_a, best_b]
